This paper discusses the history and evolution of web crawlers, which are primarily used for information retrieval (IR) and data mining (DL) purposes. The paper also mentions the use of crawlers for search engine indexing (SE) and database (DB) indexing. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of crawling modern web applications, which can be addressed using natural language processing (CL) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SE, cs.DB, and cs.CL, in that order.
